{"type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Swipe + Edge Peek Indicators\n      No bottom bar. Instead, thin accent-colored edges on left/right hint at swipeable content. On first visit, a subtle one-time animation peeks the next project card 40px in from the right, then snaps back — teaching the gesture. A floating grid button (top-right, near nav) provides the back-to-grid shortcut.\n      \n        Pros\n          No bottom bar at all — zero browser UI conflict\n          Onboarding animation teaches the gesture naturally\n          Edge indicators are minimal but discoverable\n          Grid button integrated with existing nav area\n        \n        Cons\n          Edge indicators alone may not be enough for all users\n          One-time animation only helps first-time visitors\n          Slightly more complex to implement","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1774127441950}
